The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Airline bus kills worker
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Airline bus kills worker
                            
	Chennai, July 31 (PTI): A worker was crushed to death today by a speeding bus of a private airline at Chennai International airport.        
	Siva, 33, a cleaner at the airport, was walking on a taxiway when a Paramount Airways coach returning after offloading passengers ran him over, killing him on the spot.        
	Police have arrested the bus driver.        
	In another accident at the same airport, a passenger was injured when the Jet Airways coach he was travelling in collided with a truck.                                                                                                                                                                          
